      • getTotalOutstandingAmountOnAccounts

        @Deprecated
MonetaryAmount getTotalOutstandingAmountOnAccounts()
        Deprecated. This method uses an outdated algorithm for calculating outstanding amount. For calculating outstanding amount for a particular Account use TAccountOwner.getOutstandingAmount()
        Returns:
        The total outstanding amount at the account-level for all of the producer's accounts. If an account has a negative due t-account balance (as in the case when a charge has been pre-paid), then the outstanding amount is calculated to be Max(Due + Billed, 0). If an account has a positive or zero due t-account balance, then that account's outstanding amount is Due + Billed. This method only examines the billed and due t-accounts on accounts themselves, and will not total up billed/due t-account balances on the account's policy periods.

        This method should be used in conjunction with getTotalOutstandingAmountOnPolicyPeriods(boolean) to get a total outstanding amount for all the accounts and policies for a given producer.

      • getTotalDelinquentAmountOnAccounts

        MonetaryAmount getTotalDelinquentAmountOnAccounts()
        Returns:
        the total delinquent amount on the producer's accounts. If an account has a negative due amount (as in the case when a account's charge has been pre-paid), then the account's delinquent amount will be $0

        Returns the total t-account balance of all the policies associated with this producer where the t-account pattern suffix matches the given suffix. This method can be used to find the total unbilled/billed/due amounts of all the producer's policies.
        Parameters:

      • getTotalOutstandingAmountOnPolicyPeriods

        @Deprecated
MonetaryAmount getTotalOutstandingAmountOnPolicyPeriods(boolean inForcePolicyPeriodsOnly)
        Deprecated. This method uses an outdated algorithm for calculating outstanding amount. For calculating outstanding amount for a particular PolicyPeriod use TAccountOwner.getOutstandingAmount()
        Parameters:
        inForcePolicyPeriodsOnly - If true, includes only those policies which are "in force" (effective date <= today <= expiration date) in the calculation
        Returns:
        The total outstanding amount on the producer's policy periods. If a policy period has a negative due amount (as in the case when a policy has been pre-paid), then outstanding amount is Max(Due + Billed, 0). If a policy period has a positive or zero due amount, then that policy period's outstanding amount is Due + Billed. This method only examines charges owned by PolicyPeriods, and will not include Account-level charges in its totals.

        This method should be used in conjunction with getTotalOutstandingAmountOnAccounts() to get a total outstanding amount for all the accounts and policies for a given producer.

      • becomePayerOfInvoiceItems

        void becomePayerOfInvoiceItems(ProducerCode producerCode,
                             ReversePaymentsWhenMovingInvoiceItem shouldReversePayments,
                             InvoiceItem... invoiceItems)
        Change the payer of invoiceItems to be this producer. Moves the items to this producer's statement invoices and makes this producer be the primary producer for the items.
        Parameters:
        producerCode - the producer code that will be used for the primary policy producer code for the moved items
        shouldReversePayments - if Yes, or if OnlyForNonPlanned and the item is not on a planned invoice, moves any portions of payments that were already applied to the invoice items back to unapplied.
        invoiceItems - the invoice items that the producer will become the payer of.

        numberOfDays - constrains the write-offs returned by this method to have a CreateTime no older than this.
        Returns:
        an iterable over all of the Writeoffs (item level, charge level, and producer unapplied) that are associated with this Producer and which have a CreateTime no older than numberOfDays.
